# illo Platform License v1.0.0

Effective Date: February 11, 2026

## Purpose

This license lets you view, learn from, and use this software freely
for non-competing purposes, while ensuring that any deployment of this
software maintains the creator protection features and policies that
are central to its mission.

## Acceptance

To receive this license, you must agree to all its terms. If you do not
agree, you may not use, modify, or distribute the software.

## Definitions

- **"Licensor"** means the original author(s) and copyright holder(s)
  of this software.

- **"Software"** means the illo platform software and all associated
  source code, documentation, and assets made available under this
  license.

- **"Creator Protection Features"** means the technical measures
  designed to protect uploaded works and their creators, including but
  not limited to:
  - Signed URL access control for artwork files
  - Rate limiting to prevent mass downloads
  - Detection and blocking of unauthorized access
  - Scraping and crawling prevention mechanisms
  - AI training opt-out enforcement
  - Age-restricted content gating and verification
  - Federation image quality restrictions (thumbnail-only for
    non-illo instances)

- **"Terms of Service Requirements"** means the policies governing
  user conduct and content protection, including but not limited to:
  - Prohibition of unauthorized scraping and crawling
  - Prohibition of unauthorized reposting
  - Prohibition of unauthorized AI/ML training use
  - Prohibition of circumventing technical protections
  - Content guidelines and age-restriction requirements
  - Creator copyright ownership guarantees

- **"Deployment"** means making the Software available for use by
  third parties over a network, whether publicly or within a private
  organization.

## Grant of Rights

Subject to the conditions below, the Licensor grants you a
non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free license to:

1. **View and Study** — Read and learn from the source code.

2. **Modify** — Make changes and create derivative works based on the
   Software for any Permitted Purpose.

3. **Deploy** — Run the Software or derivative works as a service,
   subject to the Deployment Conditions below.

4. **Distribute** — Distribute copies of the Software, including
   modified versions, provided that:
   - Recipients receive a copy of this license.
   - You clearly state any modifications you have made.
   - The distribution complies with all conditions of this license.

## Permitted Purpose

You may use the Software for any purpose except:

1. **Competition** — You may not use the Software to provide a product
   or service that competes with the Software or any product or service
   the Licensor provides using the Software. Products and services
   compete even when provided through different technical means,
   interfaces, or platforms; offered free of charge; or marketed under
   a different name.

2. **Removal of Protections** — You may not remove, disable, weaken,
   or circumvent any Creator Protection Features or Terms of Service
   Requirements as defined above.

## Deployment Conditions

If you Deploy the Software or any derivative work, you must:

1. **Maintain Creator Protection Features** — All Creator Protection
   Features must remain functional and enabled. You may enhance these
   features but may not reduce their effectiveness.

2. **Maintain Equivalent Terms of Service** — Your deployment must
   enforce terms of service that provide protections equal to or
   greater than the Terms of Service Requirements defined above. At a
   minimum, your terms of service must:
   - Prohibit unauthorized scraping and crawling of creator works
   - Prohibit unauthorized reposting of creator works
   - Prohibit unauthorized use of creator works for AI/ML training
   - Prohibit circumvention of technical protection measures
   - Guarantee that creators retain copyright of their uploaded works
   - Require appropriate age-restriction mechanisms for adult content

3. **Disclose Source** — You must make the complete source code of your
   deployment (including modifications) available to users of your
   service under this same license, or provide a written offer to do
   so.

4. **Attribution** — You must visibly credit the original illo project
   in your deployment (e.g., in an about page or footer).

## Noncompete Exceptions

- If the Licensor discontinues a product or service for one year or
  longer, this license does not prohibit competition with that
  discontinued product or service.

- This license does not restrict your use of the Software for internal
  tools that are not made available to third parties.

## Cure Period

The first time you are notified in writing that you have violated any
of these terms, your licenses can continue if you come into full
compliance with these terms within 32 days of receiving that notice.
The Licensor may extend this period at their discretion.

## No Sublicensing

You may not sublicense the Software. Anyone who receives a copy of the
Software from you receives their license directly from the Licensor
under the terms of this license.

